                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d799">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00 Statement July 16, 1937/174:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-11T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 11, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. Reference your telegram No. 63, August 5, 6 p.m.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d799fn20">See telegram No. 36, August 5, 6 p.m., to the Chargé in
                        Iran, <ref target="#pg_753">p. 753</ref>.</note> The Foreign Minister says
                    that he is much touched by your message and like you is gratified to note
                    similarity which exists between the policies of the United States and
                    Turkey.</p>
                <p>He asked whether he may give your message to the press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
